<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2004-03-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Immunofluorescence Assay for Serologic Diagnosis of SARS</TITLE><BODY>We evaluated a virus-infected cell-based indirect immunofluorescence assay for detecting antiâ€“severe acute respiratory syndrome-associated coronavirus (SARS-CoV) immunoglobulin (Ig) G antibody. All confirmed SARS cases demonstrated seroconversion or fourfold rise in IgG antibody titer; no control was positive. Sensitivity and specificity of this assay were both 100%. Immunofluorescence assay can ascertain the status of SARS-CoV infection.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>